page.title: 0106120216-GENERAL REVIEW
page.content: The twelve grid squares studied in this project are in an area around St. Osyth strething to the edge of the sea-side resort of Clacton-on-Sea. There is little housing and very few shops most of which are located in sections of housing estates on the fringes of the allocated area. There are two caravan parks, one called 'Meadow View',the other called 'Shangri-La'.The remainder of this area consists of woodland and arable farms. A church and small cemetry as well as several large farm houses and halls are the main historical buildings of interest.
